  "prompt": "What do you do when you are sad?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're feeling this way. While I don't have feelings, I can offer some suggestions that might help you cope with sadness:\n\n1. **Talk to Someone:** Sharing your feelings with a trusted friend, family member, or mental health professional can provide relief and perspective.\n\n2. **Engage in Physical Activity:** Exercise can boost your mood by releasing endorphins. Even a short walk can make a difference.\n\n3. **Practice Mindfulness or Meditation:** These techniques can help you stay grounded and manage overwhelming emotions.\n\n4. **Pursue a Hobby:** Engaging in activities you enjoy can distract your mind and bring a sense of accomplishment.\n\n5. **Maintain a Routine:** Keeping a regular schedule can provide structure and a sense of normalcy.\n\n6. **Express Yourself Creatively:** Writing, drawing, or playing music can be therapeutic ways to process your emotions.\n\n7. **Limit Negative Inputs:** Reducing exposure to negative news or social media can help prevent additional stress.\n\n8. **Seek Professional Help:** If your sadness persists or feels overwhelming, reaching out to a mental health professional can provide you with tailored support and strategies.\n\nRemember, it's okay to seek help, and taking the first step can make a significant difference.",
